core-task.info: Run predefined tasks whenever watched files change.

task.summary: Default task
adding the resource files to git
got horsey working great, need to style it. something else fixed just dont remember what
horsey works but won't allow click. need to fix later.
set up local dev enviro way better - use js.js as server with db.json as db
dev setup very well off, saving and creating now save to file as well
icons and nav links aligned, new page button added to nav menu, editor hide/show moved to left.
buttons and markdown cheatsheet improvements
commented out keyword section for edit/create content since no input available yet.
domStore.js renamed to dom.js, nav items' hr removed, createPage will work - for now only with section pages
unused variable DOM removed
saving and creating more realistic with delay in local mode, save button changes affect inner element instead of overwriting with just text now, Content.prototype.save is now .savePage
save button styles removed/reset when clicked
better equipped to handle local dev environment.
toggle editor "button" is now a basic link almost, active link color adjusted on nav, local dev improved/corrected (data variable accidental insertion in complete()).
buttons styled, navbar better styling with padding, alignments, markdown-it settings adjusted (no code highlighting necessary).
better styling for editor toggle and (this was a couple commits ago but...) external links inside of #ph-output now open in new window/tab
tables in #ph-output have 1em margin top/bottom

hide "Overview" header on top-level pages by storing numeric "level" property and using for comparison. will also use this later when revising nav links code potentially. reduced items pulled during initial load (no need to pull all the content texts for all the pages - only need keywords, refs and the other metadata).
markdown editor theme change.
fixed external links opening in new window code. how dumb was i lol
re-worked external new window link opening for cross-browser support-ish (aka IE)
integrated postcss into grunt workflow - autoprefixer was main reason. removed excess prefixes from source CSS files
made it easier to change search input placeholder text because it was mentioned yesterday
clean up and data transmit code fixed in case filename changes on server.
going headfirst into the lions den of messing around with stuff. wish me luck.

incredibly large amount of changes, should have committed forever ago. options able to be set on the site, defaults kept in code, empty tabs are hidden, pop-up notifying about this change on by default, events object moved to its own file, beginnings of: user permission checking to determine download of editor files, much higher utilization of virtual-dom and "Add content" page.
add a teaser so people don't just think I left a blank page on accident.

The teaser broke stuff so I had to go fix. Oddly enough much more came from this than expected. More v-dom integration and getting closer and closer to the finish line (well, for the adding content fiasco that is).

fixed action on cheatsheet button click, fixed box-sizing issue on navbar, added keymap in editor for Ctrl-S to save, started adding more detailed comments, options and state for pages and DOM respectively adjusted/cleaned.

title element is now contenteditable and saves with rest when saving, much better performance (almost too good) clicking nav links since switching from DOM manipulation to virtual-dom manipulation, border around current tab, colored empty tabs pink
had to remove keyword references til I know how to utilize it.
make it obvious the title can be edited in-place

for some stupid reason IE 11/10 refuse to abide by my 17px to the right on the navbar. probly something to do with overflows or something but for now it's fixed (for IE - chrome doesn't render properly now).
rendering and models optimized a little more, external links in output open in new window/tab again, "Last modified: ..." now displays at bottom of pages
nav menu css and HTML cleaned up, set editor toggle to take over page (remove navbar) for more room

re-worked virtual-dom rendering to include a bit more, more responsive feel, full screen view while editing (may have done in previous commit actually), better event handling (title input takes ENTER now to blur), content add button and wrapper added to #ph-content and open/close functionality added.
better styling for navbar (font sizes and padding mainly), hide search if viewing content editor
new site-provided options added - hideNav/SearchWhileEditing. self-explanatory.
current tab does not react to an :active state.
tab contrib setup getting closer. navbar padding and adjustments reverted then fixed again, this time using more generic labels (ph-level-2, 3, 4 etc)
oops, almost forgot to disable clicking that hidden link.
minor adjustments - title element states + bottom border behavior modified with better logic, contrib POC link now doesnt allow clicking if hidden, also changed text from POC Name to CTA.
much better styling of nav elements, beginning setup on wrapper fixed to not use try{} catch{}
title can be saved to server on blur now, removed dependency to lodash throughout code (wasn't much effect on size of code), renamed DOM.loadContent() more appropriately to DOM.update()
minor arrangements and tidiness.

window.scroll() added on content change to go back to top of content, only works in chrome for now (something preventing in IE, will check later), removed eventemitter2 in favor of much smaller event lib, other minor updates
just slight font change
